- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and sequence-to-sequence models. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a new architecture for neural networks. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with uncertainty in inputs, which is a common problem in AI. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper experiments with speech translation lattices. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also a less likely category, but possible as the paper deals with representing alternative sequences and their probabilities in a compact form.
